<h2 id="my-nagging-boss">My Nagging Boss</h2>
<p>Turns out anytime we jumped on a call and talked about business, there was a 50% chance of us arguing. It was a lot of my partner telling me what to do, scolding me for doing something wrong or for not listening clearly. I knew nothing about this wedding dress business so I was very naive. I had to constantly remind myself to not take things personally and to find a healthy way of communicating with her.</p>

<p>Ideally, personal and business can be separated just like on the T.V. show, How I Met Your Mother. Whenever Lily and Marshall got into an argument they could pause their argument at any time to kiss and make up and continue the argument at a later time â¤. Sadly that is not how real life works and often times an argument can leave a bitter taste.</p>

<p>However, thatâ€™s just a tiny unpleasant fraction of this whole experience. I admire my partner so much for what sheâ€™s accomplished and what sheâ€™s capable of. Iâ€™ve learned so much from her and was tasked with building a Shopify store as well as handling all operations in the U.S. including customer service, shipping, and cleaning.</p>

